==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-conjecture.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-both}}

# A statement or idea which has not been [[proven]], but is thought to be true; a [[guess]].
#:''I explained it, but it is pure '''conjecture''' whether he understood, or not.''

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[gissing]] ''f.'', [[giswerk]] ''n.''
*Italian: [[congettura]]
*Portuguese: [[conjetura]] {{f}}
*Swedish: [[förmodan]] {{c}}
*German: [[Vermutung]] {{f}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|conjectur|ing}}

# {{intransitive}} To [[guess]]; to [[venture]] an unproven idea.
#: ''I don't know if it is true, I'm just conjecturing here.''

====Translations====
*Dutch : [[gissen]]
*Portuguese: [[conjeturar]]

